        "content": "<p>We have <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=map_nonneg#doc\">docs#map_nonneg</a> (about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=OrderAddMonoidHomClass#doc\">docs#OrderAddMonoidHomClass</a>) and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=NonnegHomClass.map_nonneg#doc\">docs#NonnegHomClass.map_nonneg</a> (exported to the root namespace). <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/10472\">#10472</a> changes <code>import</code>s so that both are available in many files. Which one should stay in the root namespace?</p>",
